<br>
Head over to the Overthere from the Frontier Mountains zone, after a breif walk you will come to a drop off  called the ledge, this will be your home base.<br>
<br>
There are many mobs that wonder this hillsaide from blue to red, everything from Sarnaks to Cockatrice. You will be after the Sabretooth tigers and rhinos which seem most abundant. Most of the Sabretooths con blue or even to me at 33, and most of the rhinos are yellow.<br>
<br>
Once you find your prey, (a yellow rhino is best) start out with your usual snare tactic. Do you remember that semi useless spell terrorize animal? Well now is the time to use it, cast it on the snared rhino and begin to nuke away. Every hit causes the beast to turn around and walk back the other way so you can stand in one spot and just unload your mana on the fool without taking a hit or kiting it all over the zone. The fear will usually wear out 1 or 2 nukes from its death, so either kite it normally or recast fear and there ya go, if you are low on mana cast fear and med till it wears off and you should be able to finish it off.<br>
<br>
I know that necros fear kite all the time, but I dont see druids do it very much so I hope you find this useful in your quest for 60. This is just a tactic I have found to be useful, and I don't expect everyone to like it or anything so no flames please.<br>
<br>
